{"title_page": "William Eadie (footballer)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2017}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = William Eadie\n| fullname = \n| birth_date = 14 June 1882\n| birth_place = [[Dunblane]], Scotland\n| death_date = {{death date and age |1915|4|23|1882|6|14|df=yes}}<ref name=\"CWGC\" />\n| death_place = [[Gravenstafel Ridge (Ypres)|Gravenstafel Ridge]], [[Ypres salient]], Belgium\n| height = \n| position = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| years1 = 1900\u20131903\n| clubs1 = [[Queen's Park F.C.|Queen's Park]]\n| caps1 = 12\n| goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 1906\u2013\n| clubs2 = [[St Mirren F.C.|St Mirren]]\n| caps2 = 1\n| goals2 = 0\n| years3 = {{0|0000}}\u20131908\n| clubs3 = Dunblane\n| caps3 = \n| goals3 = \n| years4 = 1908\u20131911\n| clubs4 = [[Partick Thistle F.C.|Partick Thistle]]\n| caps4 = 5\n| goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 1913\n| clubs5 = [[East Fife F.C.|East Fife]]\n| caps5 = \n| goals5 = \n}}\n'''William P. Eadie''' (14 June 1882 \u2013 23 June 1915), also known as '''William Prince''', was a Scottish professional [[association football|football]] [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] who played in the [[Scottish Football League|Scottish League]] for [[Queen's Park F.C.|Queen's Park]], [[St Mirren F.C.|St Mirren]] and [[Partick Thistle F.C.|Partick Thistle]].<ref name=\"Edinburgh\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.scotlandswar.co.uk/pdf_Season_1914-1915_(Fell).pdf |title=They Died in the Conflict during Season 1914\u20131915 |accessdate=15 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nEadie was born in [[Dunblane]], Scotland had three brothers who each played football \u2013 [[James Eadie (footballer)|James]] (Dunblane, [[Queen's Park F.C.|Queen's Park]]),<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.qpfc.com/appearances/e/eadiej.htm |title=QPFC.com \u2013 A Historical Queen's Park FC Website |website=www.qpfc.com |accessdate=31 July 2016}}</ref> David and Alexander (both Strathallan).<ref name=\"SSH\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.scottishsporthistory.com/sports-history-news-and-blog/the-footballer-known-as-prince-the-strange-tale-of-william-eadie |title=The footballer known as Prince \u2013 the strange tale of William Eadie |website=Scottish Sport History \u2013 devoted to our sporting heritage |accessdate=31 July 2016}}</ref> On 20 March 1914, he emigrated to Canada.<ref name=\"SSH\" /> One month after the outbreak of the [[First World War]], he enlisted in the [[10th Battalion (Canadians), CEF|10th Battalion]] of the [[Canadian Expeditionary Force]] at [[CFB Valcartier]].<ref name=\"SSH\" /> He enlisted under the name of William Prince and was [[killed in action]] at [[Gravenstafel Ridge (Ypres)|Gravenstafel Ridge]] near [[Saint-Julien, Langemark|Saint-Julian]], [[Western Front (World War I)|Belgium]] on 23 April 1915 on the second day of the [[Second Battle of Ypres]].<ref name=\"SSH\" /> He is commemorated on the [[Menin Gate]] and the [[Saint Julien Memorial|Saint-Julian Memorial]].<ref name=\"SSH\" /><ref name=\"CWGC\">{{CWGC|id=1591941|accessdate=30 July 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Honours ==\n'''Dunblane'''\n* Perthshire Cup: 1905\u201306<ref name=\"SSH\" />\n\n== Career statistics ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Club\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Season\n! colspan=\"3\" |League\n! colspan=\"2\" |Scottish Cup\n! colspan=\"2\" |Total\n|-\n!Division\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |[[Queen's Park F.C.|Queen's Park]]\n|[[1902\u201303 Scottish Division One|1902\u201303]]<ref name=\"QPFC\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.qpfc.com/appearances/e/eadieaw.htm |title=QPFC.com \u2013 A Historical Queen's Park FC Website |website=www.qpfc.com |accessdate=4 June 2017}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[Scottish Football League First Division|Scottish First Division]]\n|2\n|0\n|0\n|0\n|2\n|0\n|-\n|[[1904\u201305 Scottish Division One|1904\u201305]]<ref name=\"QPFC\" />\n|8\n|0\n|1\n|0\n|9\n|0\n|-\n|[[1905\u201306 Scottish Division One|1905\u201306]]<ref name=\"QPFC\" />\n|2\n|0\n|0\n|0\n|2\n|0\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" |Total\n!12\n!0\n!1\n!0\n!13\n!0\n|-\n|[[St Mirren F.C.|St Mirren]]\n|[[1906\u201307 Scottish Division One|1906\u201307]]<ref name=\"Litster\">{{Cite book |title=Record of Pre-War Scottish League Players |last=Litster |first=John |publisher=PM Publications |location=Norwich}}</ref>\n|Scottish First Division\n|1\n|0\n|0\n|0\n|1\n|0\n|-\n|[[Partick Thistle F.C.|Partick Thistle]]\n|[[1908\u201309 Scottish Division One|1908\u201309]]<ref name=\"Litster\" />\n|Scottish First Division\n|5\n|0\n|0\n|0\n|5\n|0\n|-\n! colspan=\"3\" |Career total\n!18\n!0\n!1\n!0\n!19\n!0\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Eadie, William}}\n[[Category:1882 births]]\n[[Category:1915 deaths]]\n[[Category:Scottish footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football goalkeepers]]\n[[Category:Queen's Park F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Scottish Football League players]]\n[[Category:Canadian Expeditionary Force soldiers]]\n[[Category:St Mirren F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Partick Thistle F.C. players]]\n[[Category:East Fife F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Canadian military personnel killed in World War I]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Dunblane]]\n\n\n{{Scotland-footy-goalkeeper-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2017}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = William Eadie\n| fullname = William P. Eadie<ref name=\"Edinburgh\" />\n| birth_date = 14 June 1882\n| birth_place = [[Dunblane]], Scotland\n| death_date = {{death date and age |1915|4|23|1882|6|14|df=yes}}<ref name=\"CWGC\" />\n| death_place = [[Gravenstafel Ridge (Ypres)|Gravenstafel Ridge]], [[Ypres salient]], Belgium\n| height = \n| position = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| years1 = 1900\u20131903\n| clubs1 = [[Queen's Park F.C.|Queen's Park]]\n| caps1 = 12\n| goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 1906\u2013\n| clubs2 = [[St Mirren F.C.|St Mirren]]\n| caps2 = 1\n| goals2