{"title_page": "Rwenzori turaco", "text_new": "{{Taxobox\n| name = Rwenzori turaco\n| image = GallirexJohnstoniKeulemans.jpg\n| status = LC\n| status_system = IUCN3.1\n| status_ref = <ref name=iucn>{{cite iucn |publisher=[[IUCN]] |author=BirdLife International |author-link=BirdLife International |date=2016 |title=''Gallirex johnstoni'' |page=e.T22688373A93195141 |url=https://www.iucnredlist.org/species/22688373/93195141 |doi=10.2305/IUCN.UK.2016-3.RLTS.T22688373A93195141.en}}</ref>\n| kingdom = [[Animalia]]\n| phylum = [[Chordata]]\n| classis = [[Aves]]\n| ordo = [[Musophagiformes]]\n| genus = Ruwenzoronis\n| authority = Neumann, 1903\n| species = johnstoni\n| authority = ([[Richard Bowdler Sharpe|Sharpe]], 1901)\n| synonyms =\n*Tauraco johnstoni\n}}\n\nThe '''Rwenzori turaco''' (''Ruwenzoronis johnstoni'') is a [[bird]] in the family [[Musophagidae]]. It occurs in [[Afromontane]] forests of [[Burundi]], [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]], [[Rwanda]], and [[Uganda]].<ref name=iucn/>\n\nIt is [[monotypic]] within the genus ''Ruwenzoronis''.<ref>{{cite book |author=del Hoyo, J. |author2=Collar, N.J. |author3=Christie, D.A. |author4=Elliott, A. |author5=Fishpool, L.D.C. |last-author-amp=yes |year=2014 |title=HBW and BirdLife International Illustrated Checklist of the Birds of the World. Volume 1: Non-passerines |publisher=Lynx Edicions, BirdLife International |location=Barcelona, Spain and Cambridge}}</ref>\n\nThe Rwenzori turaco is a [[herbivorous]] bird: about 92% of its diet consists of fruit and 6.3% of leaves.<ref name = \"Sun\">{{cite journal|first=C. |last=Sun|first2= T. C.|last2= Moermond |first3= T. J. |last3=Givnish |title=Nutritional Determinants of Diet in Three Turacos in a Tropical Montane Forest |journal=The Auk |volume=114 |issue=2 |url=http://sora.unm.edu/sites/default/files/journals/auk/v114n02/p0200-p0211.pdf |year=1997 |pages=200\u2013211 |jstor=4089161|doi=10.2307/4089161}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Turacos}}\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q1101389}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:turaco, Rwenzori}}\n[[Category:Musophagidae|Rwenzori turaco]]\n[[Category:Birds of Sub-Saharan Africa]]\n[[Category:Birds described in 1901|Rwenzori turaco]]\n[[Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Species of bird}}\n{{Speciesbox\n| name = Rwenzori turaco\n| image = GallirexJohnstoniKeulemans.jpg\n| status = LC\n| status_system = IUCN3.1\n| status_ref = <ref name=iucn>{{cite iucn |publisher=[[IUCN]] |author=BirdLife International |author-link=BirdLife International |date=2016 |title=''Gallirex johnstoni'' |page=e.T22688373A93195141 |url=https://www.iucnredlist.org/species/22688373/93195141 |doi=10.2305/IUCN.UK.2016-3.RLTS.T22688373A93195141.en}}</ref>\n| genus = Gallirex\n| parent_authority = Neumann, 1903\n| species = johnstoni\n| authority = ([[Richard Bowdler Sharpe|Sharpe]], 1901)\n| synonyms =''Ruwenzorornis johnstoni'', ''Musophaga johnstoni''\n}}\n\nThe '''Rwenzori turaco''' (''Gallirex johnstoni'') is a [[bird]] in the family [[Musophagidae]]. It occurs in [[Afromontane]] forests of [[Burundi]], [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]], [[Rwanda]], and [[Uganda]].<ref name=iucn/>\n\nIt is [[monotypic]] within the genus ''Gallirex''.<ref>{{cite book |author=del Hoyo, J. |author2=Collar, N.J. |author3=Christie, D.A. |author4=Elliott, A. |author5=Fishpool, L.D.C. |last-author-amp=yes |year=2014 |title=HBW and BirdLife International Illustrated Checklist of the Birds of the World. Volume 1: Non-passerines |publisher=Lynx Edicions, BirdLife International |location=Barcelona, Spain and Cambridge}}</ref>\n\nThe Rwenzori turaco is a [[herbivorous]] bird: about 92% of its diet consists of fruit and 6.3% of leaves.<ref name = \"Sun\">{{cite journal|first=C. |last=Sun|first2= T. C.|last2= Moermond |first3= T. J. |last3=Givnish |title=Nutritional Determinants of Diet in Three Turacos in a Tropical Montane Forest |journal=The Auk |volume=114 |issue=2 |url=http://sora.unm.edu/sites/default/files/journals/auk/v114n02/p0200-p0211.pdf |year=1997 |pages=200\u2013211 |jstor=4089161|doi=10.2307/4089161}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Turacos}}\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q1101389}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:turaco, Rwenzori}}\n[[Category:Musophagidae|Rwenzori turaco]]\n[[Category:Birds of Sub-Saharan Africa]]\n[[Category:Birds described in 1901|Rwenzori turaco]]\n[[Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot]]\n", "name_user": "119.237.203.92", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rwenzori_turaco"}
{"title_page": "Koshish (TV series)", "text_new": "{{Use Indian English|date=May 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2015}}\n{{more citations needed|date=April 2012}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = Koshish - Ek Aashaa\n| image                = Koshish (TV series).jpg\n| picture_format       = [[480i]] \n| runtime              = approx. 22 minutes\n| creator              = [[Balaji Telefilms]]<br />[[Endemol India]]\n| writer               = '''Story & Screenplay'''<br />R M Joshi, Vipul Mehta, Bhavin Patel & Mahesh Pandey<br />'''Dialogues'''<br />Sunjoy Shekhar \n| director             = [[Anurag Basu]]<br/>Hemant Prabhu\n| editor               = Dharmesh Shah, Vinay Malu, Sandeep Dharne\n| cinematography       = Sanjay Memane\n| producer             = [[Ekta Kapoor]]<br/>[[Shobha Kapoor]]\n| starring             = Sandhya Mridul, Varun Badola\n| opentheme            = \"Woh Aashaa Hai\"\n| composer          = Lalit Sen\n| country              = India\n| network              = [[Zee TV]]\n| first_aired          = February 2000\n| last_aired           = April 2002\n| num_episodes         = 117\n}}\n\n'''''Koshish - Ek Aashaa''''' is an [[India]]n [[soap opera]] that aired on [[Zee TV]] from 2000-2002. It won the award for 'Best Soap Opera' at the RAPA Awards in 2001.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.indiantelevision.com/headlines/y2k1/june/june24.htm|title=Zee Bags three RAPA Awards|work=Indiantelevision.com|date=18 June 2001}}</ref>\n\n==Overview==\nKajal is a young woman who gets married on the insistence of her mother. She has not met the man prior to the wedding. However, on the wedding night, Kajal discovers that the man is actually a mentally challenged person who has the mind of an eight year old. She realises that she has been tricked into marrying him by her in-laws. This makes her furious. Kajal wants to tell her mother, but she cannot because her mother is a heart patient. Kajal is unwilling to accept this marriage and blames her in-laws for ruining her life. Neeraj is innocent and childlike. Kajal finds it hard to tolerate his behaviour, because of which their relationship has quite a turbulent start. After spending some time together, however, Kajal and Neeraj become close. Kajal's mother finds out about the situation and forces Kajal to come back home. Neeraj panics since he can't stay without Kajal, who also doesn't want to leave him. Kajal's mother files a case against Neeraj's family. But, Kajal refuses to leave Neeraj. This strengthens their bond. Kajal comes back and starts her mission to cure Neeraj. She consults a specialist doctor who assists her in treating Neeraj. Gradually, Kajal becomes suspicious that someone in the family doesn't want Neeraj to get cured, but she isn't sure who the person is since everyone seems to love Neeraj a lot. Neeraj's doctor advises Kajal to take Neeraj to a medical camp which could help cure him. Kajal and Neeraj go, although Neeraj's father opposes the idea. When they come back, everyone is surprised at how much Neeraj has improved. All is going well, until on Neeraj's birthday, someone attacks him and he gets hurt on his head. This causes him to regress back into his earlier condition. Kajal is shattered, yet, she refuses to give up hope. She takes Neeraj to the United States for treatment. When they return, Neeraj is fully recovered. He is able to attend office, make his own decisions and understand everything. Kajal and Neeraj are able to live their marital life properly, and express their love to each other. Kajal becomes pregnant, because of which everyone is overjoyed. However, some misunderstandings occur between Kajal and Neeraj, which leads to them having an argument. Kajal has an accident and loses her child. She also loses her memory partially. Soon, it is revealed that Kajal was only pretending to have lost her memory to protect herself from the person who was responsible for Neeraj's condition. That person is Neeraj's mother, who is actually his stepmother. She was the person who killed Neeraj's grandfather, and made him mentally unstable. The reason behind all of this was the fact that Neeraj is the heir to all of his grandfather's property, which his stepmother wanted for herself and her real children. Neeraj's stepmother dies as a result of poisoning, and so does his father. A few years later, Kajal and Neeraj are shown talking to each other about their lives. Neeraj thanks Kajal for supporting him and never giving up on him. They also have a daughter, who they named Asha. The show concludes on a happy note that everything is fine now, all because of Kajal's efforts (koshish).\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Sandhya Mridul]] as Kaajal\n* [[Varun Badola]] as Neeraj\n* [[Jaya Bhattacharya]] as Suniti\n* [[Anupam Bhattacharya]] as Sudhir\n* [[Savita Prabhune]] as Rekha\n* [[Prachi Shah]] as Bhavana\n* [[Shubhangi Gokhale]] as Kaajal's mother\n* Rajesh Tandon as Ishaan\n* [[Uday Tikekar]] as Niraj's father\n* [[Shital Thakkar]] as Kaajal's sister\n* [[Aditi Pratap]] as Niraj's sister\n* [[Shweta Kawatra]]\n* Sai Ballal\n* Mirza Zohaib Alam\n* [[Suchita Trivedi]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links==\n*[http://www.rajshri.com/zee/koshish/index.asp?Page=12 Watch online]\n\n{{Zee TV Programmes}}\n{{Balaji Telefilms}}\n\n[[Category:Balaji Telefilms television series]]\n[[Category:Indian television soap operas]]\n[[Category:Zee TV television series]]\n[[Category:2000 Indian television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2002 Indian television series endings]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Indian English|date=May 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2015}}\n{{more citations needed|date=April 2012}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = Koshish - Ek Aashaa\n| image                = Koshish (TV series).jpg\n| picture_format       = [[480i]] \n| runtime              = approx. 22 minutes\n| creator              = [[Balaji Telefilms]]<br />[[Endemol India]]\n| writer               = '''Story & Screenplay'''<br />R M Joshi, Vipul Mehta, Bhavin Patel & Mahesh Pandey<br />'''Dialogues'''<br />Sunjoy Shekhar \n| director             = [[Anurag Basu]]<br/>Hemant Prabhu\n| editor               = Dharmesh Shah, Vinay Malu, Sandeep Dharne\n| cinematography       = Sanjay Memane\n| producer             = [[Ekta Kapoor]]<br/>[[Shobha Kapoor]]\n| starring             = Sandhya Mridul, Varun Badola\n| opentheme            = \"Woh Aashaa Hai\"\n| composer          = Lalit Sen\n| country              = India\n| network              = [[Zee TV]]\n| first_aired          = February 2000\n| last_aired           = April 2002\n| num_episodes         = 117\n}}\n\n'''''Koshish - Ek Aashaa''''' is an [[India]]n [[soap opera]] that aired on [[Zee TV]] from 2000-2002. It won the award for 'Best Soap Opera' at the RAPA Awards in 2001.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.indiantelevision.com/headlines/y2k1/june/june24.htm|title=Zee Bags three RAPA Awards|work=Indiantelevision.com|date=18 June 2001}}</ref>\n\n==Overview==\nKajal is a young woman who gets married on the insistence of her mother. She has not met the man prior to the wedding. Howvever, on the wedding night, Kajal discovers that the man is actually a mentally challenged person who has the mind of an eight year old. She realises that she has been tricked into marrying him by her in-laws. This makes her furious. Kajal wants to tell her mother, but she cannot because her mother is a heart patient. Kajal is unwilling to accept this marriage and blames her in-laws for ruining her life. Neeraj is innocent and childlike. Kajal finds it hard to tolerate his behaviour, because of which their relationship has quite a turbulent start. After spending some time together, however, Kajal and Neeraj become close. Kajal's mother finds out about the situation and forces Kajal to come back home. Neeraj panics since he can't stay without Kajal, who also doesn't want to leave him. Kajal's mother files a case against Neeraj's family. But, Kajal refuses to leave Neeraj. This strengthens their bond. Kajal comes back and starts her mission to cure Neeraj. She consults a specialist doctor who assists her in treating Neeraj. Gradually, Kajal becomes suspicious that someone in the family doesn't want Neeraj to get cured, but she isn't sure who the person is since everyone seems to love Neeraj a lot. Neeraj's doctor advises Kajal to take Neeraj to a medical camp which could help cure him. Kajal and Neeraj go, although Neeraj's father opposes the idea. When they come back, everyone is surprised at how much Neeraj has improved. All is going well, until on Neeraj's birthday, someone attacks him and he gets hurt on his head. This causes him to regress back into his earlier condition. Kajal is shattered, yet, she refuses to give up hope. She takes Neeraj to the United States for treatment. When they return, Neeraj is fully recovered. He is able to attend office, make his own decisions and understand everything. Kajal and Neeraj are able to live their marital life properly, and express their love to each other. Kajal becomes pregnant, because of which everyone is overjoyed. However, some misunderstandings occur between Kajal and Neeraj, which leads to them having an argument. Kajal has an accident and loses her child. She also loses her memory partially. Soon, it is revealed that Kajal was only pretending to have lost her memory to protect herself from the person who was responsible for Neeraj's condition. That person is Neeraj's mother, who is actually his stepmother. She was the person who killed Neeraj's grandfather, and made him mentally unstable. The reason behind all of this was the fact that Neeraj is the heir to all of his grandfather's property, which his stepmother wanted for herself and her real children. Neeraj's stepmother dies as a result of poisoning, and so does his father. A few years later, Kajal and Neeraj are shown talking to each other about their lives. Neeraj thanks Kajal for supporting him and never giving up on him. They also have a daughter, who they named Asha. The show concludes on a happy note that everything is fine now, all because of Kajal's efforts (koshish).\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Sandhya Mridul]] as Kaajal\n* [[Varun Badola]] as Neeraj\n* [[Jaya Bhattacharya]] as Suniti\n* [[Anupam Bhattacharya]] as Sudhir\n* [[Savita Prabhune]] as Rekha\n* [[Prachi Shah]] as Bhavana\n* [[Shubhangi Gokhale]] as Kaajal's mother\n* Rajesh Tandon as Ishaan\n* [[Uday Tikekar]] as Niraj's father\n* [[Shital Thakkar]] as Kaajal's sister\n* [[Aditi Pratap]] as Niraj's sister\n* [[Shweta Kawatra]]\n* Sai Ballal\n* Mirza Zohaib Alam\n* [[Suchita Trivedi]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links==\n*[http://www.rajshri.com/zee/koshish/index.asp?Page=12 Watch online]\n\n{{Zee TV Programmes}}\n{{Balaji Telefilms}}\n\n[[Category:Balaji Telefilms television series]]\n[[Category:Indian television soap operas]]\n[[Category:Zee TV television series]]\n[[Category:2000 Indian television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2002 Indian television series endings]]\n", "name_user": "Jcoolbro", "label": "safe", "comment": "Howvever->However -Fix a typo in one click", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Koshish_(TV_series)"}
